<HEADLINE>
FT  14 SEP 93 / World Commodities Prices: Tea
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The Tea broker's Association reports, Landed good demand. Quality Assams
sold well at firm to dearer rates but others were irregular with plainer
North Indians often easier. Bright and coloury medium East Africans were
well supported and prices tended higher. Plainer types remained firm.
Ceylons met good competition but prices were often 2 to 4p easier. Offshore
good demand at firm rates. Quotations: quality 200p/kg nom, good medium
128p/kg, medium 112p/kg, low medium 93p/kg the highest price realised this
week was 253p for an Assam
</TEXT>
