<HEADLINE>
FT  14 SEP 93 / International Company News: Nordic groups plan cement merger
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By CHRISTOPHER BROWN-HUMES
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   HELSINKI
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
THREE Nordic groups plan to merge their cement activities to create a new
regional force in the building materials sector in the face of the collapse
in construction activity.
Sweden's Euroc is buying Partek Cement and Lohja from the Finnish companies
Partek and Metra. In return the two Finnish groups will receive 11.8m new
shares in Euroc worth SKr1.2bn (Dollars 153m). This gives them a 25 per cent
holding in Euroc, equal to the stake held by Skanska, Sweden's leading
construction and property group.
Mr Finn Johnsson, Euroc president said: 'Each one of our companies is too
small to create the resources needed for necessary investments in plants,
new technology, research, environmental measures and product development.
Taken together we have overcapacity of around 50 per cent, against 25 to 30
per cent in the rest of Europe.'
He said that there would be substantial rationalisation as a result of the
merger, including the possible closure of a cement plant in Sweden and
another in Finland. Mr Johnsson said the target was to cut costs by SKr200m
a year from 1996.
</TEXT>
