FT  14 SEP 93 / World Trade News in Brief: Keypad dumping case rejected
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By LISA BRANSTEN
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   WASHINGTON
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
The International Trade Commission yesterday ruled that an Italian maker of
pads that cushion the movement of keys on woodwind instruments did not
injure his US competitor, Lisa Bransten writes from Washington. Mr Giuseppe
Prestini of Arizona said an Italian rival was selling keypads in the US for
less than fair market value. The ITC ruled against Mr Prestini 5-1 in what
is considered to be the smallest dumping case ever to come before the trade
panel.
