<HEADLINE>
FT  14 SEP 93 / Trichet departure prompts financial administration reshuffle
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JOHN RIDDING
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Mr Trichet's departure from the head of the Treasury, has prompted a
reshuffle at the top of France's financial administration. His post is to be
taken by Mr Christian Noyer, the director of Mr Alphandery's private office,
John Ridding reports.
Mr Noyer, 42, has a similar background to Mr Trichet, who is 50. Both are
graduates of the elite Ecole Nationale d'Administration and both have spent
most of their careers in the financial administration. Mr Noyer will be
replaced in the private office of Mr Alphandery by Mr Patrice Vial. Mr Vial,
previously a chief forecaster in the economics ministry, is currently
director general of Banque Pallas-Stern, the French merchant bank.
