FT  13 SEP 93 / Welsh boundary changes attacked
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
BOUNDARY changes designed to increase the number of Euro constituencies in
Wales from four to five were attacked yesterday by Mr Alex Carlile, Liberal
Democrat MP for Montgomery.
He said they involved creating new constituencies through merging Gwynedd
and Dyfed and Powys and Clwyd which were 'geographically and demographically
incompatible'.
Mr Carlile attributed the 'madcap scheme' to the short-circuiting of normal
procedures so that the new boundaries could be in place in time for next
year's European parliamentary elections.
